<!-- FAQ -->
<section style="padding:72px 24px;background:#EAF5FB;">
  <div style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;">
    <span class="kicker">FAQ</span>
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="font-size:clamp(24px,3.5vw,36px);margin:0 0 32px;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:16px;">
      <div style="background:#fff;border-radius:14px;padding:24px 28px;box-shadow:0 3px 12px rgba(10,61,92,0.06);">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 10px;">How much does egress window installation cost in Lincoln, NE?</h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#5A6B76;margin:0;">Most jobs fall between $2,500 and $5,500, depending on your foundation thickness, the window size required, and the window well material you choose. We give you a firm written estimate after a site visit, so there's no guessing.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border-radius:14px;padding:24px 28px;box-shadow:0 3px 12px rgba(10,61,92,0.06);">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 10px;">Do I need a permit for an egress window in Lincoln?</h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#5A6B76;margin:0;">Yes, cutting a new egress opening or enlarging one for a basement bedroom requires a permit through Lincoln-Lancaster County. We handle the permit paperwork and make sure the finished install meets code before we close out the job.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border-radius:14px;padding:24px 28px;box-shadow:0 3px 12px rgba(10,61,92,0.06);">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 10px;">How long does egress window installation take?</h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#5A6B76;margin:0;">Most single-window cut-ins are done in one day, from opening the foundation to setting the window well and grading drainage. Larger jobs, unusual foundation walls, or multiple windows can take longer, and we'll walk you through the timeline at your estimate.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border-radius:14px;padding:24px 28px;box-shadow:0 3px 12px rgba(10,61,92,0.06);">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 10px;">Can you install an egress window in winter?</h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#5A6B76;margin:0;">Yes, we install egress windows year-round, though frozen or heavily saturated ground can add time to the excavation. We'll tell you upfront if winter conditions are likely to affect your specific site.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border-radius:14px;padding:24px 28px;box-shadow:0 3px 12px rgba(10,61,92,0.06);">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 10px;">Do you offer after-hours or rush service?</h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#5A6B76;margin:0;">We keep a 24/7 line open for closing deadlines, failed inspections, and flooded window wells. Rush and after-hours work typically adds $150 to $400 to the job depending on timing and scope, and we'll confirm that cost before we start.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff;border-radius:14px;padding:24px 28px;box-shadow:0 3px 12px rgba(10,61,92,0.06);">
        <h3 style="font-family:'Nunito Sans',sans-serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:800;color:#0A3D5C;margin:0 0 10px;">Will a new egress window make my basement bedroom legal?</h3>
        <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.75;color:#5A6B76;margin:0;">An egress window is one requirement for a legal basement bedroom, but sizing, sill height, and well dimensions all have to meet code together. We size every install to current requirements so the room can pass inspection as a legal bedroom.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

